review_blob: Amazing beer. I love how its a dark beer, big body and has a nice peanut butter with chocolate taste to it. the hope go well and it is so well balanced that you can taste everything. Nothing is over power. I strongly recommend it, as you can smell the chocolate as you take the beer in.

This beer is so smooth. I love the big brown foam head to it that goes with the black motor look of a body. Its a big body beer that is smooth that goes down, has a nice little smoked taste to it and will leave you a nice after taste. It is very well balanced between the smoked flavor, the smooth feel to it and such a good amount of malt. Definitely a beer I will buy again.
beer_name: North Coast Old Rasputin Russian Imperial Stout

review_blob: Pours to a dark, black body with a very nice aroma of chocolate malts. The first sip starts with a smooth malty, chocolate flavor and finishes with a harsh bitter roasted coffee. Very well rounded beer from a new kid on the block.
This is a good light beer with light body and golden color. Very little head and a slight smell of hops, a little citrusy too.

The beer is simple. It has a dark red, medium body with very little foam and very little carbonation. Very nice hopes and smooth taste to it. Goes down easy and great IPA that is light for the summer.
beer_name: Latitude 42 Red Beards India Red Ale

review_blob: Had this in a bottle. Pours to a solid gold bottle with a citrusy aroma to it with a medium body. Not much carbonation with a small head o it. The only downside for me I was expecting this to be a bit hoppier, though it has a nice grapefruit taste to it
beer_name: Terrapin Side Project Hopzilla Double IPA

review_blob: Bottle. Nice medium body with a slight head and some carbonation. Starts off with some malty, chocolate taste to it. The after taste gives you a nice roast that lingers a bit on the front of your tongue. Very nice
beer_name: Coronado / Cigar City Jurata Baltic Porter

review_blob: A full body with a motor oil color for appearance with a nice liquor taste. This is a perfect desert beer that should be enjoyed and not chugged like any normal beer. Very nice oak barrel taste to and did they do a great job of aging it. The prefect beer to enjoy at the brewery
Nice and easy summer beer. Simple with a light body with a hint of earthly smell to it. Went down easy

This is by far my favorite pilsner through everything Ive tried. Its clean, crisp and goes down easy Not much carbonation to this, though the head was a little foamy. The beer really comes into its own after letting it breathe for 20-30 minutes. Strongly recommend this.

This is a smooth and nice brewed beer. nice, sweet smell with a smooth finish to the beer. it has a good milk and creamy taste for it. Not overpowering and well recommended it to anyone going to boscos.
UPDATED: JUN 21, 2014

Falls short on all front. The aroma is rather weak with a strong pine nut taste that overpowers the citrus flavor of your typical IPAs. Rather thin in body while being rather cardonated. Didnt much care for it.
The name is rather misleading as I was expecting a beer with hops slammed down my throw. Rather this is a type IPA, nice citrus taste and smell but nothing more.

Absolutely loved this beer. Pours to a dark, big body and smells of sweet liquor but is well balanced. Has a sweet liquor taste mixed in with the malts and a hint of fig, really didnt taste the date in this but the alcohol is hid very well. Not overpowering like others. My favorite barley wine
UPDATED: MAY 19, 2010

This is a big body beer that has taste of maple and vanilla that do a great job of hiding the alcohol in taste but like others have said, the alcohol will creep up on you. The aroma is a faint but it goes to how purpose of this beer. Loved it and goes down very smooth as the maple, vanilla and oak is well balanced with not being overpowering.

Not quite sure what the beers look like as I drank this straight from the can and it taste dead with some of the beer IPAs. The aroma is your typical citrusy type but the taste is very crisp, clean and goes down easy with a hint of the hops lingering on the back of your throat but in a good way. Nothing that is overpowering and I strongly recommend this

absolutely loved this beer and still cant believe that it comes in a can. The aroma is filled with chocolate and a coffee malts. This is a full body that is pitched black and as thick as motor oil when you pour. The taste is smooth with chocolate and roasted coffee.

Quite a tasty ipa with a full amber body, filled with citrus and pine hopes, mixed in with malts. Nice flavor the only down side is that it doesnt go down smooth but it does have a nice lingering taste, nothing to harsh on the pallet.
Pours to a dark, amber body, a bit carbonated for a stone but this has a strong hoppy, taste to it, the only down side to this is the last lingers. A step away from being a IPA
UPDATED: MAY 19, 2010

This is by far my favorite of the group, it has an medium amber body with a very sweet cirtus aroma to it. Very faint head to it that disappears fast but the beer if filled with malts mixed in with hops, a hint of spice in them along with caramel and  a floral taste to it. Loved it

very pleased with this porter. Nice dark brown body to it, very little carbonated, well balanced between the malts that leave you with a slight taste of char mixed with some chocolate, didnt get any caramel like others suggested but very good. Almost forgot, this is medium body beer. Wouldnt mind going back for another

While the heading says Imperial IPA, for me this comes across more as a strong IPA with a nice citrus aroma to it with a tad bit more hops, giving it a somewhat stronger smooth to taste to these floral and citrus hops that fill the beer.
UPDATED: APR 8, 2013

Absolutely loved the malts and caramel taste to this thick body that is a desert beer, meant for enjoying. the aroma is rich with malts, a slight hint of sugar. amazing beer, cant think of one negative to say about it. Great with a nice steak
UPDATED: JAN 15, 2011

Loved tjhis peer, the body is cloudy and a nice white foam head that dissipated quickly. Its a medium body with hints of belguim sugar, fruits and finished with a nice, smooth taste. The aroma is mixed between all this, very nice blend and balanced, a little more carbonated than most beers in this category but great all around.
Smells like a typical domestic beer, pours to a copper orange body, light body beer that is slight carbonated with a hint of caramel
I loved the malty, roasted taste to this copper body beer, medium body and with a touch of tops to it. slightly carbonated
Pours to a orange-copper body, large white foam head and is heavily carbonated with a slight hint of pumpkin and cinnamon to it. Very light body beer

review_blob: Pours to a white head, clear orange body. Very crisp taste with a bitter taste of pinenuts and grapefruit. Balanced well and goes down smooth. Loved it.

This beer is a simple lager with a hint of tstrawberry taste to it. very light ody beer that is easy to drink

by far this is my favorite hefe beer, its not a typical but rather has a hint of hops mixed in with your wheat flavor and a banana with a tad bit of hops that very good summer beer

pours to a copper body with very little head and a sweet floral aroma to it. The body is medium with a bitter hop taste that stays with you, all in all, the pine nuts are a good taste to blend in with the hops but this is a hair bit more bitter than i like.
